  <section class="section">
    <div class="container service-layout">
      <article>
        <p class="eyebrow red">Overview</p>
        <h2>Controlled entry for doors, offices, gates, and managed properties.</h2>
        <p>Access control reduces key problems, improves accountability, and lets property operators manage who can enter specific spaces.</p>
        <div class="notice">A site survey is the correct starting point. System design depends on construction type, code requirements, communication path, existing equipment, and the customer's response expectations.</div>
        <h3>Typical scope</h3>
        <ul class="text-list"><li>Card readers and mobile credentials</li>
<li>Door controllers and schedules</li>
<li>Electric strikes and maglock coordination</li>
<li>User provisioning and removal</li>
<li>Audit trails</li>
<li>Integration with video and intrusion systems</li></ul>
        <h3>How the work proceeds</h3>
        <div class="process">
          <div><h3>Survey</h3><p>Walk the property and define coverage, risk, and communication requirements.</p></div>
          <div><h3>Design</h3><p>Select equipment, monitoring path, placement, and response workflow.</p></div>
          <div><h3>Install</h3><p>Install, test, label, document, and train users.</p></div>
          <div><h3>Monitor</h3><p>Connect signals to monitoring and maintain the system over time.</p></div>
        </div>
      </article>
